                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf.184.01502/83: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to Lieutenant Colonel <persName type="to">E. J. Dawley</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-01">August 1,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Misc. 1155. Your telegram of July 28th, quoting letter signed by Gough, Boset,
                    and Dawley acknowledged. Your participation in this letter not understood by
                    American Commission, in view of fact that the sole function of American Baltic
                    Commission is to observe and report on economic, political and military
                    situations. Your undated personal telegram to General Bliss, Supreme War
                        Council,<note n="57" xml:id="d73fn57">Not printed.</note> acknowledged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
